# QUICK FIX – Roadside Assistance Service

**Tagline**  
Turning roadside emergencies into effortless recoveries.

Imagine a world where roadside assistance is seamless and stress-free.

![Hero Banner](https://via.placeholder.com/1200x600/000000/FF6600?text=QUICK+FIX+-+Roadside+Assistance)  
*(Dark background with orange accents, stranded car & tow truck illustration)*

**Brand Identity**  
- Primary Color: Orange (#FF6600)  
- Secondary: Black (#000000)  
- Accent: White (#FFFFFF)  
- Logo: Orange gear + car silhouette

## Project Overview

This project focuses on digitally transforming a traditionally non-digital roadside assistance service in India into a modern, user-centered mobile-first experience.

We identified major pain points:  
- Severe lack of real-time data & transparency  
- Slow response times & poor communication  
- Reliance on unstructured partner networks  
- Limited accessibility in smaller cities  

The solution is a seamless digital platform that streamlines booking, tracking, payments, and service delivery — improving satisfaction for users and operational efficiency for providers.

## Design Process (Double Diamond)

Discover ──► Define ──► Design ──► Deliver
Insights     Problem      Ideation      Solution
Observations   Statement                 Feedback

## Project Timeline

| Phase      | Duration   | Key Activities                          |
|------------|------------|-----------------------------------------|
| Discover   | 5 days     | Research, Insights, Observations        |
| Define     | 2 days     | Problem Statement                       |
| Design     | 3 days     | UI/UX ideation, wireframes, visuals     |
| Deliver    | 3 days     | High-fidelity prototypes, feedback      |

**Total: ~13 days**

## DISCOVER Phase – Key Insights (India Context)

- **40%** of car owners in India have comprehensive insurance policies (many still lack roadside coverage)  
- **~120 million** people (≈8% of population) owned cars in 2022  
- **62.69%** of breakdowns caused by non-start issues (battery, fuel, etc.)  
- Roadside assistance market expected to grow at **~4.1% CAGR** (2022–2030 globally)

**Core Problem**  
Severe lack of structured data collection, real-time tracking, and easy digital access — leaving drivers vulnerable during breakdowns.

